        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37016",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wilmoore",
                        "name": "wilmoore",
                        "displayName": "Wil Moore III (wilmoore)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Seems like something that could be resolved using unit tests with a special grouping. Exclude the \"requirements\" group from \"AllTests\" and include this group in something like \"AllRequirments\". Provide user documentation on how to run this set of tests from the command-line.\r\n\r\nIf this is approved it can be assigned to me.\r\n\r\nI'd love to hear other suggestions if the above isn't a viable solution.\r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wilmoore",
                        "name": "wilmoore",
                        "displayName": "Wil Moore III (wilmoore)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-18T00:21:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-18T00:21:06.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37019",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It should be a provider for Zend_Tool.\r\n{code}\r\nzf check requirements\r\n{code}\r\nBut the requirements depends on the components really used.\r\nThomas Weidner use something to update our requirements tables in documentation but I can't remember the name of the tool.\r\n\r\nEdit: it's PHP_CompatInfo",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-18T01:02:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-18T01:21:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37021",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mhujer",
                        "name": "mhujer",
                        "displayName": "Martin Hujer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I primary meant it as a single php file which you can easily run on your hosting to determine if it is suitable for ZF.\r\n\r\nIf it is going to be a part of Zend_Tool or unit tests, it wouldn't be so easy to run it there.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mhujer",
                        "name": "mhujer",
                        "displayName": "Martin Hujer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-18T01:19:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-18T01:19:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37047",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wilmoore",
                        "name": "wilmoore",
                        "displayName": "Wil Moore III (wilmoore)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": ">> If it is going to be a part of Zend_Tool or unit tests, it wouldn't be so easy to run it there.\r\n\r\nMartin,\r\n\r\nThis is exactly why I suggested the phpunit approach -- if you have shell access with your host, you should be able to run phpunit; however, after reading Mickael's latest comment regarding PHP_CompatInfo and looking into the component, I think it would be fairly straight-forward to create a PHP script that runs through the requirements.\r\n\r\nThe toughest part is deciding what to test for since requirements depend on what components you want to use. I suppose the tool could run through everything and report what you can and can't use based on your environment.\r\n\r\nSuch a tool might end up being pretty cool.\r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wilmoore",
                        "name": "wilmoore",
                        "displayName": "Wil Moore III (wilmoore)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-18T09:04:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-18T09:04:02.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37049",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mhujer",
                        "name": "mhujer",
                        "displayName": "Martin Hujer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I have updated link to Nette Requirements Checker - that's what I think that this tool should do (+display, which ZF components won't work properly because: ...)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mhujer",
                        "name": "mhujer",
                        "displayName": "Martin Hujer",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-18T09:11:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-18T09:13:06.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37057",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wilmoore",
                        "name": "wilmoore",
                        "displayName": "Wil Moore III (wilmoore)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thanks for the updated link. This could be a really nice component actually. I would suggest a web and command-line interface. I'd be willing to work on this but I would need some guidance as to the correct approach since there doesn't seem to be anything documented as to conventions for something that needs a full blown web interface (or I just don't know where to look).\r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wilmoore",
                        "name": "wilmoore",
                        "displayName": "Wil Moore III (wilmoore)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-18T11:01:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-18T11:01:04.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37058",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wilmoore",
                        "name": "wilmoore",
                        "displayName": "Wil Moore III (wilmoore)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Example of software that implements the requested feature.\n\nhttp:\/\/translate.google.com\/translate?js=y&prev=_t&hl=en&ie=UTF-8&layout=1&eotf=1&u=http%3A%2F%2Fwiki.nettephp.com%2Fcs%2Fpozadavky-frameworku&sl=cs&tl=en",
